In the history of Yu-Gi-Oh, Jackpot 7 OTK decks require you to go second. What if I told you that you can also go first with this deck besides going second? Let me show you:

 

1) Draw a lot of cards with Panda and Saryuja or Librarian and Formula until you reach the situation illustrated below. Don't forget to set all three Jackpot 7 cards.

  • Special Summon Yajiro to the middle via Saryuja. If you summon Yajiro elsewhere, it will be destroyed. Be careful with that.
  • Yajiro is here to destroy everything within his sight while trying to catch up any monster you are trying to summon. It's the main idea for this deck.
  • If you are out of summoning charges with Panda, use "Pot of Avarice".

 

2) Play Yajiro >>> Shien's Spy combo to place him into the 1st column. There, you can do this in order:

  • Panda >>> Monster into 5th column >>> Yajiro moves to 2nd column >>> First Jackpot 7 destroyed!
  • Imduk into 4th column by using 5th column monster >>> Yajiro moves to 3rd column >>> Second Jackpot 7 destroyed!
  • Panda >>> Monster into 4th/5th column >>> Yajiro moves to 4th column >>> Third Jackpot 7 destroyed!

 

3) Congratulations, you win the game!

 

As always, here are the tips for saving up some SR and UR points:

- "Into the Void" can be found within "The Infinite Void" Secret Pack to save 90 SR!

- "Pot of Avarice" can be collected by purchasing "Re-Contact Universe" deck. 90 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Jackpot 7" can be found within "Legacy Pack". I hope you really hit the jackpot, where you can save up to 90 SR!

- "Wonder Wand" and "Spellbook of Knowledge" can be collected by purchasing "Spellbook of Prophecy" deck. 120 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Moray of Avarice" can be unlocked through timed selection pack called "The Synchronized Cosmoc". As of this writing, if you are willing to spend gems to save 30 UR, this is your chance.

- "Link Spider", "Link Bound" and LAN are given for free, if you've picked "Link Generation". Thus, 90 SR is saved!

- "Formula Synchron" isn't really needed, if you are low on SR. Though it can be unlocked by opening "Stardust Ties" Secret Pack, Saryuja and other Link monsters can pick targets to refill GY for "Pot of Avarice" more than enough. 90 SR saved!

- "T.G. Hyper Librarian" can be found within "Futuristic Creatures" Secret Pack to save 30 UR. However, you don't need to bother with him at all, if you don't want to spend SR on "Formula Synchron".

- "Number 60: Dugares the Timeless" can be found within "Number Recall" Secret Pack. If you play Saryuja >>> Monk >>> Panda combo and target Monk+Panda to XYZ summon him, you can draw two more cards. Number 60 is really good card to thin your deck but you don't have to spend 30 SR on him, if you are low on SR.

 

So, in total, you can save up to 600 SR and 60 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

 

That's all for this one. Let me know if you have any questions and have fun in Master Duel!

Clerk & Child special themselves for free, Sister search Revenge is a 1 card Elf and Sister + any Gagaga can make a Rank 4. Nothing except Sister is OPT. 

Downsides would be that you don't really have a good Gagaga target to summon via Gigantic so if you already opened everything Spright related it's a bit awkward and Clerk, Child & Revenge need other Gagaga cards to be useful so if you draw multiple of one but nothing else it's a brick. Furthermore, while this version was definitely never optimal anyway the fact you can't get any use out of Sprind means it's considerbly worse in comparison than it used to be. 

Bystials also are quite detrimental as they can just run over both Anubis & Rai-Oh wich is why i decided to go for Avramax over Goddess to try and mitigate that issue. At least Bystials can be utilized by this deck itself rather well and with Jet & Blue being semi limited you pretty much have the exact space to run all the good ones.

I decided to go for only Double Cross without Smashers as i think the card is honestly quite a bit better and i didn't really run into situations were i missed Smashers.

Exciton is something i wanted to try as Tear isn't the only thing on ladder anymore atm and it sounded pretty cracked going 2nd. Not sure if replacing Dugares for it is actually worth it tho.

This is Springans Deck.

Honestly the side deck might need some work but this deck struggles against backrow so siding hate against it is needed.

The deck doesnt need its normal summon except with Kitt but thats if you dont open with Golgonda & thats why Lava Golem is pretty great with the deck.

Spright smashers is kinda bricky but can come in clutch sometimes so its debatable to just run it at 1 or just switch it out with handtraps.

2 King Regulus seems pretty good, debating on running on 3 but seems kinda bricky so 2 is the sweet spot.

Number 60 is in the extra just for the OTK potential when you need that extra atk boost.

End Board is Giant Sargas, Captian Sargas, Time Thief, Regulus & sometimes abyss dweller or gear gigant for the extender next turn
